Which of the following pairs of sample size n and population proportion p would produce the greatest standard deviation for the sampling distribution of a sample proportion~$\overset{\wedge}{p}$?
(A) n = 1,000 and p close to 0
(B) n = 1,000 and p close to 1
(C) n = 1,000 and p close to~$\dfrac{1}{2}
(D) n = 100 and p close to 0
(E) n = 100 and p close to~$\dfrac{1}{2}
